section#quickstart
  .container.py-5
    h2.h-anchor#buildingwithbbot Building with bBot
    .row
      .col-md-4
        h3 #[include /img/code.svg] Alpha Release
        p bBot alpha is in active development.
        p We're streamlining our docs and developer tools for writing, deploying and interacting with bBot instances as a matter of priority.
        p For now, the quickest way to get started is to start a new local project, import bBot and start chatting in the command line.
      .col-md-8
        h3 #[include /img/play.svg] Quick Start
        .page-content.mb-4
          p 1. bBot is a #[a(href="npmjs.com/package/bbot") Node.js package], so it requires #[a(href="https://www.npmjs.com/get-npm") Node and NPM]
          p 2. Start a new project with #[code npm init]
          p 3. Install bBot as a dependency with #[code npm install --save bbot]
          p 4. Create an #[strong index.js] file as per example below
          p 5. Run the bot with #[code node index.js]
      .col-12
        h3 #[include /img/message.svg] Hello World
        p Create an #[b index.js] for a simple #[i hello] <whoever> chatbot...
        pre
          code.language-js
            | const bot = require('bbot')
            | 
            | bot.listenText(/say Hello World/, (b) => {
            |   b.respond(`Hello World!`)
            | })
            | 
            | bot.start()
        p Test interactions by chatting in your terminal...
        pre.code-container
          code.shell
            img(src="/img/hello-content.png" width="100%")
    hr
    a.btn.btn-secondary(href="/docs/core") See more docs
